[thinking] **Exploring annotation handling**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about how source annotation types might have the same binary name if they share the package/class. Could that lead to using different class loaders? It seems like using getAnnotation(Class) on Element compares names, which is interesting! I wonder if I can utilize classes from runtime even if the annotation type in source has a matching qualified name. However, I'm pondering how the source can't declare a class already on the classpath. I'll need to look further into existing native image tests and how they utilize the compiler.
