[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about using BatchCompiler for annotation processing. I need to check if the ECJ version supports Java 17. Version 3.26.0 from Eclipse 2021 likely supports Java 16. I wonder if my test source needs to avoid modern features since it’s compiled by JDK 21. Using the correct source and target version is essential—maybe I should consider passing -source 11 and -target 11 to keep it simple. I also need to ensure my class names follow naming rules.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Exploring class naming rules**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering how the naming rules apply to test class or file names versus inner classes. It looks like generating top-level helper classes could help. I might go with package-private top-level classes to minimize inner name usage, while keeping one public top-level test class. I wonder if I can have a package-private processor in the same file. It seems important to maintain a one-to-one mapping between the dynamic-access report classes and the generated test class files.
